00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:39,700
 Paul explains it very clearly.

363
00:14:39,700 --> 00:14:41,300
 He tells Timothy,

364
00:14:41,300 --> 00:14:47,100
 "Timothy, you must be strong in the one side of Jesus Christ."

365
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:48,700
 If you pay attention,

366
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:52,400
 both the later and earlier books of Timothy

367
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:55,700
 are very personal books

368
00:14:55,700 --> 00:15:00,100
 especially given to Paul and Suleiman.

369
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:02,200
 One of the sons is Timothy,

370
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:04,200
 and the other is Tithon.

371
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:07,700
 But these two books are different.

372
00:15:07,700 --> 00:15:09,100
 The content of the books

373
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:14,100
 is very different from that of Tithon and Timothy.

374
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:15,800
 The tone of the words is also different.

375
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:16,700
 Why?

376
00:15:16,700 --> 00:15:18,000
 Because it is very simple.

377
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:21,100
 Paul knew these two sons.

378
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:23,800
 He even knew their personalities.

379
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:26,000
 Timothy was a good boy.

380
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:28,500
 Timothy was a relatively weak person.

381
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:30,100
 He was introverted.

382
00:15:30,100 --> 00:15:32,700
 He grew up in a Christian family.

383
00:15:32,700 --> 00:15:35,300
 But the problem was that he had not gone through the storm.

384
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:36,400
 Because of this reason,

385
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:38,400
 what did he need most?

386
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:39,300
 He saw him.

387
00:15:39,300 --> 00:15:44,200
 What you need most is actual experience.

388
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:51,300
 The appearance you get from your mother's faith

389
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:53,600
 is completely correct.

390
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:54,900
 But is it enough?

391
00:15:54,900 --> 00:15:57,500
 Paul tells him, "You are not strong."

392
00:15:57,500 --> 00:15:59,100
 Because of this,

393
00:15:59,100 --> 00:16:03,000
 when he saw this family living for a very short time,

394
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,900
 he felt their bottom.

395
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:05,900
 What is the bottom?

396
00:16:05,900 --> 00:16:08,300
 It is not just social relations.

397
00:16:08,300 --> 00:16:09,500
 "Have you eaten?"

398
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:10,400
 "Good morning."

399
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:11,300
 "How are you?"

400
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:11,900
 "I am fine."

401
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:13,400
 No.

402
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:15,900
 It is not even a deep relationship.

403
00:16:15,900 --> 00:16:16,900
 A deep relationship means

404
00:16:16,900 --> 00:16:19,300
 that you know the deep things in your heart.

405
00:16:19,300 --> 00:16:23,400
 You know how their original family is.

406
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:26,500
 Paul had to enter the spiritual realm.

407
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:28,400
 In our group today,

408
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:30,100
 I want to tell you

409
00:16:30,100 --> 00:16:32,300
 not to pretend

410
00:16:32,300 --> 00:16:35,500
 that no one knows your original family.

411
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:36,900
 Your struggle,

412
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:38,800
 your struggle in the spiritual realm,

413
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:41,500
 we have to enter the spiritual realm.

414
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:42,800
 We have to use the words of God,

415
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:44,100
 our experience,

416
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:46,700
 the experience of some brothers and sisters,

417
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:48,000
 and the experience of the ancestors.

418
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:49,900
 We have to encourage each other.

419
00:16:49,900 --> 00:16:52,100
 This is what we have to do today.

420
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:55,300
 So we can see clearly here

421
00:16:55,300 --> 00:16:58,100
 that Paul is applying the Great Mission.

